What is a variable in Python?
A variable in Python is a name given to a memory location that is used to store data values. It acts as a reference or container to store information,
 which can then be used and manipulated within a program.

 Explain the difference between a list and a tuple.
A list is a mutable (changeable) sequence of elements that can hold items of different types. Lists are defined using square brackets [] while
A tuple is an immutable (unchangeable) sequence of elements, which means once a tuple is created, its values cannot be changed. Tuples are defined using parentheses ()

